  <releases>
    <release version="2.0.0" date="2025-10-04">
      <description>
        <p>Major update: Online Multiplayer with extensive improvements</p>
        <p>NEW: Online Multiplayer Features</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Play draughts online against opponents worldwide</li>
          <li>Host private game rooms with unique room codes</li>
          <li>Quick match system for instant random opponent pairing</li>
          <li>Session persistence - reconnect to games after disconnections</li>
          <li>Server crash recovery with automatic reconnection</li>
          <li>Support for all 16 game variants in multiplayer</li>
          <li>Timer support in online games (Fischer and Bronstein modes)</li>
          <li>Real-time game synchronization via WebSocket</li>
          <li>Opponent disconnect/reconnect notifications</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Board and Gameplay Improvements</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Adaptive board orientation - your pieces always appear at the bottom</li>
          <li>Works in single-player (color selection) and multiplayer</li>
          <li>Proper piece highlighting based on current player in multiplayer</li>
          <li>Fixed captured pieces synchronization in online games</li>
          <li>Improved board perspective transformations</li>
        </ul>
        <p>UI/UX Enhancements</p>
        <ul>
          <li>New multiplayer dialog with modern ViewStack navigation</li>
          <li>StatusPages with helpful descriptions for all multiplayer screens</li>
          <li>Connection status indicators in header bars</li>
          <li>Toast notifications for opponent connection events</li>
          <li>Pill-shaped action buttons in bottom header bars</li>
          <li>Back navigation buttons with arrow icons</li>
          <li>Settings initialized from user preferences in multiplayer</li>
          <li>Removed welcome screen for streamlined experience</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Bug Fixes</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Fixed duplicate game end dialogs in multiplayer</li>
          <li>Fixed timer not working in multiplayer games</li>
          <li>Fixed variant selection bug (Brazilian â†’ American)</li>
          <li>Fixed server crash causing application crashes</li>
          <li>Fixed quick match self-pairing issues</li>
          <li>Improved error handling for offline servers</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Technical Improvements</p>
        <ul>
          <li>WebSocket-based multiplayer networking with libsoup-3.0</li>
          <li>Node.js relay server with room management</li>
          <li>JSON-based protocol for all multiplayer messages</li>
          <li>Quick match queue system organized by variant</li>
          <li>Added node_modules to .gitignore</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="1.0.1" date="2025-10-03">
      <description>
        <p>Mobile-friendly update with improved adaptive design and bug fixes</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Full mobile and tablet support with 360px minimum width</li>
          <li>Adaptive dialogs with breakpoints for narrow screens</li>
          <li>Game History dialog now uses bottom sheet for filters on mobile</li>
          <li>Game Replay dialog optimized with side panel as bottom sheet</li>
          <li>Speed controls moved to overflow menu on mobile devices</li>
          <li>New Game dialog now properly scrollable on small screens</li>
          <li>Fixed timer expiration crash - game now ends properly when time runs out</li>
          <li>Improved touch-friendly margins and spacing on mobile</li>
          <li>Better adaptive bottom bar with priority-based element hiding</li>
          <li>All dialogs now work seamlessly at mobile screen sizes</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="1.0.0" date="2025-10-02">
      <description>
        <p>First stable release of Draughts - A comprehensive draughts/checkers game</p>
        <ul>
          <li>16 international game variants: American Checkers, International, Russian, Brazilian, Italian, Spanish, Czech, Thai, German, Swedish, Pool, Turkish, Armenian, Gothic, Frisian, and Canadian</li>
          <li>10 AI difficulty levels from Beginner to Grandmaster with intelligent move evaluation</li>
          <li>Three gameplay modes: Human vs Human, Human vs AI, and AI vs AI</li>
          <li>Complete sound effects system with audio feedback for moves, captures, and game events</li>
          <li>PDN (Portable Draughts Notation) export for game analysis and sharing</li>
          <li>Four piece styles: Plastic, Wood, Metal, and Bottle Cap</li>
          <li>Five board themes: Classic, Wood, Green, Blue, and High Contrast</li>
          <li>Full move history with unlimited undo/redo support</li>
          <li>Smooth animations and visual feedback for all game actions</li>
          <li>Keyboard navigation and screen reader accessibility support</li>
          <li>Comprehensive rules documentation for each variant</li>
          <li>Modern GTK4/LibAdwaita interface with adaptive design</li>
          <li>Dark mode support following system theme</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
